content:
The CRM Analytics Watchlist gives users the advantage of capturing and tracking up to 20 KPIs across different dashboards, plus historical trending. No more switching between dashboards to see what has changed, and track your metrics all in one place.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

To manage a watchlist: Use CRM Analytics
NOTE Enable Dashboard Views must be on to use Watchlists. The feature is enabled by default.

Access the Watchlist. Each user can save up to 20 metrics to their Watchlist.
Add a dashboard item to the Watchlist by clicking the widget dropdown menu and selecting Add to Watchlist.
Type in name for the Watchlist metric and define how changes are tracked.
Save, delete or edit a Watchlist metric as needed.

Watchlist metrics include last snapshot date, snapshot frequency, date metric was added, and source dashboard.
Metrics can be organized in any desired order by clicking Change Order at the bottom of the metrics listing and dragging to new position.

Note: Watchlist metrics can only come from dashboards you have access to. The Watchlist can only display an itemâ€™s metric value starting from the time it was added.
title: Monitoring Important Metrics with CRM Analytics Watchlist
